<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-625-346  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 625 346.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  May 17 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for networks: DCA introduces IRMALAN for NetWare. (DigitalCommunications Associates Inc.) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Communications Associates Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    DCA.andO;Product:   IRMALAN for NetWare (Computer network software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionLocal Area NetworksSoftware PackagesGateways (Connector).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR NETWORKS: DCA Introduces IRMALAN For NetWare ALPHARETTA, GEORGIA,U.S.A., 1990 MAY 15 (NB) -- While hinting at further product announcements inadvance of the Spring Comdex show, which opens June 3, Digital CommunicationsAssociates has introduced IRMALAN for NetWare, a family of gateway serverproducts for the IPX/SPX local area network operating system.andM;The products include a new memory management utility that allows computerslinked to a network to emulate an IBM 3270 mainframe terminal using as littleas 28,000 bits of memory taken from a hard disk or expanded and extendedmemory.andP;  According to DCA, &quot;this breaks the 640K barrier&quot; for network users,letting them give all system memory to applications.andP;  With the memorymanagement product installed, there can be 5 concurrent sessions between alocal network and a mainframe.andM;Doug Lifton, director of product management for DCA's 3270 business unit,explained.andP;  &quot;What happens with the memory management software is the utilityis first loaded into memory, and then you load the LAN (local area network)software.andP;  To use the memory management utility, you would swap the emulatorinto extended or expanded memory, or the hard disk drive.&quot;andM;Mike Van Frayen, product manager for IRMALAN, was asked if the newannouncement conflicts with DCA's announced Select Server project, ajoint-development with Microsoft.andP;  &quot;We don't think it conflicts in anyfashion.andP;  Our desire is to create a broad range of choices.andP;  This gateway isDOS-based.andP;  Our relationship with Microsoft is on the OS/2 side.&quot;andM;While IRMALAN for NetWare is strictly a DOS product, there is speculationthat it will work with Windows 3.0 when that product is announced.andP;  DCAofficials refused to comment on Windows 3.0, but said specifically theproduct does not work well with the current version of Windows.andP;  Also, whilethe product is designed for NetWare 286, it is expected to function withNetWare 386 as well.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19900515/Press Contact: Bill Marks, DCA, 404- 442-4520)</TEXT></DOC>